abstract: In the end, Joe Biden, who bills himself as the most electable candidate in the 2020 U.S. Democratic presidential field, could not convince nearly enough Iowans that he is the best person to take on President Donald Trump in November.
snippet: In the end, Joe Biden, who bills himself as the most electable candidate in the 2020 U.S. Democratic presidential field, could not convince nearly enough Iowans that he is the best person to take on President Donald Trump in November.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — In the end, Joe Biden, who bills himself as the most electable candidate in the 2020 U.S. Democratic presidential field, could not convince nearly enough Iowans that he is the best person to take on President Donald Trump in November.
headline_main: Rosy Polls but Few Yard Signs: How Joe Biden Stumbled in Iowa
headline_print_headline: Rosy Polls but Few Yard Signs: How Joe Biden Stumbled in Iowa

abstract: SOMERSWORTH, N.H. — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Wednesday unleashed direct and explicit attacks on Pete Buttigieg and Senator Bernie Sanders, both of whom he is badly trailing in partial Iowa caucus results, arguing that Mr. Sanders would drag down other Democratic candidates and chiding Mr. Buttigieg for playing down the accomplishments of the Obama administration.
lead_paragraph: SOMERSWORTH, N.H. — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Wednesday unleashed direct and explicit attacks on Pete Buttigieg and Senator Bernie Sanders, both of whom he is badly trailing in partial Iowa caucus results, arguing that Mr. Sanders would drag down other Democratic candidates and chiding Mr. Buttigieg for playing down the accomplishments of the Obama administration.

abstract: Pete Buttigieg held a narrow lead over Bernie Sanders on Tuesday in long-delayed results from the chaotic Iowa Democratic Party caucuses, and former Vice President Joe Biden trailed badly in fourth place with about 71% of precincts reporting.
snippet: Pete Buttigieg held a narrow lead over Bernie Sanders on Tuesday in long-delayed results from the chaotic Iowa Democratic Party caucuses, and former Vice President Joe Biden trailed badly in fourth place with about 71% of precincts reporting.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa/LACONIA, N.H. — Pete Buttigieg held a narrow lead over Bernie Sanders on Tuesday in long-delayed results from the chaotic Iowa Democratic Party caucuses, and former Vice President Joe Biden trailed badly in fourth place with about 71% of precincts reporting.
